Nor aught in such a moment could it avail the luckless girl that she had first bestowed on the king the name of father. For listed up in the hands of the men she was carried shivering to the altars, not after due performance of the customary rites to be escorted by the clear-ringing bridal song, but in the very season of marriage stainless maid mid the stain of blood to fall a sad victim by the sacri- ficing stroke of a father, that thus a happy and prosperous departure might be granted to the fleet. So great the evils to which religion could prompt!
